00:00:00,040 --> 00:00:14,740
( Watch on Kissasia.vip )

1
00:00:00,959 --> 00:00:03,837
As if they were born on different planets,

2
00:00:04,337 --> 00:00:06,214
there are two people who are completely different.

3
00:00:07,549 --> 00:00:08,466
Could these two

4
00:00:08,925 --> 00:00:10,468
ever fall in love?

5
00:00:11,094 --> 00:00:12,303
Nonsense.

6
00:00:13,096 --> 00:00:15,140
Unless their souls swapped bodies.

7
00:00:20,979 --> 00:00:25,900
"Check In to You"

8
00:00:27,277 --> 00:00:31,656
(Episode 1: Who Are You?)

9
00:01:56,908 --> 00:02:02,413
We blended 45% Guatemala, 30% Colombia,
and 25% Ethiopia.

10
00:02:06,668 --> 00:02:08,962
Increase the Ethiopia by 5%.

11
00:02:08,962 --> 00:02:10,421
Yes, understood.

12
00:02:16,886 --> 00:02:18,680
I'll be on my way, then.

13
00:02:23,017 --> 00:02:24,352
Hey!

14
00:02:26,271 --> 00:02:28,439
Here are the hot dogs.
One hot dog set.

15
00:02:28,439 --> 00:02:29,524
Be careful in the rain.

16
00:02:29,816 --> 00:02:31,901
High five with uncle before you go, princess.

17
00:02:33,278 --> 00:02:34,487
Have a safe trip.

18
00:02:35,822 --> 00:02:37,407
- Drive safely.
- I will.

19
00:02:37,407 --> 00:02:39,951
- Make sure to eat the hot dogs!
- Okay.

20
00:02:39,951 --> 00:02:40,827
Whoa!

21
00:02:42,871 --> 00:02:45,874
How about a hot morning instead of a hot dog, boss?

22
00:02:45,874 --> 00:02:48,459
It's noon, not morning.

23
00:02:48,459 --> 00:02:50,545
Oh yeah, a hot noon!

24
00:02:58,428 --> 00:03:01,055
And I told you, I'm not the boss.
I'm the manager.

25
00:03:01,055 --> 00:03:02,932
Right, right.

26
00:03:02,932 --> 00:03:04,851
Manager Yoon Jio.

27
00:03:06,561 --> 00:03:08,187
Then who's the boss?

28
00:03:08,438 --> 00:03:09,397
I don't know.

29
00:03:09,522 --> 00:03:10,356
You don't?

30
00:03:10,565 --> 00:03:13,401
The boss changed last year,
but I've never seen them.

31
00:03:13,401 --> 00:03:14,611
We've never even spoken on the phone.

32
00:03:14,861 --> 00:03:17,071
Do they own so many places they just forgot?

33
00:03:17,822 --> 00:03:19,699
The previous boss told me

34
00:03:19,949 --> 00:03:23,077
that the new boss
is young, and their face...

35
00:03:23,077 --> 00:03:24,913
- Huh?
- is practically glowing.

36
00:03:25,496 --> 00:03:26,205
Awesome.

37
00:03:26,205 --> 00:03:28,833
- On top of that, their character...
- Good character too?

38
00:03:29,834 --> 00:03:31,628
It's apparently outstanding.

39
00:03:32,295 --> 00:03:34,339
Then what is the second thing I hate the most?

40
00:03:34,339 --> 00:03:35,548
Making mistakes.

41
00:03:35,548 --> 00:03:38,134
No, that's the third.

42
00:03:38,968 --> 00:03:40,511
Punctuality?

43
00:03:41,471 --> 00:03:43,014
Fourth.

44
00:03:45,934 --> 00:03:48,144
Needless waste.

45
00:03:48,269 --> 00:03:50,313
Ah... yes.

46
00:03:50,313 --> 00:03:54,692
But you just committed my second,
third, and fourth biggest pet peeves all at once.

47
00:03:54,692 --> 00:03:55,944
You made a mistake,

48
00:03:55,944 --> 00:03:58,613
which made us waste time, money, and energy,

49
00:03:58,613 --> 00:04:00,823
and now we're going to be late.

50
00:04:00,823 --> 00:04:02,200
I apologize.

51
00:04:02,200 --> 00:04:06,079
I'll never make a mistake,
waste anything, or be late...

52
00:04:07,455 --> 00:04:09,374
Weren't we going there without an appointment?

53
00:04:11,668 --> 00:04:13,336
I made a promise to myself.

54
00:04:13,336 --> 00:04:14,712
That I'd get there within an hour.

55
00:04:14,963 --> 00:04:16,422
Ah... right.

56
00:04:18,549 --> 00:04:19,717
Well,

57
00:04:19,717 --> 00:04:21,761
at least you can act like a proper boss.

58
00:04:22,053 --> 00:04:24,472
But I'm seriously curious...

59
00:04:24,722 --> 00:04:26,766
What is the number one thing you hate?

60
00:04:26,766 --> 00:04:28,601
You... never told me.

61
00:04:30,770 --> 00:04:32,730
Clinging to things that don't make money,

62
00:04:33,398 --> 00:04:35,608
and calling it "values."

63
00:04:36,567 --> 00:04:40,697
I'm sure they're someone who values
meaning more than money.

64
00:04:40,947 --> 00:04:43,491
That's why they trusted me with this place
for over a year.

65
00:04:43,491 --> 00:04:46,577
A perfectly flawless person actually exists.

66
00:04:46,577 --> 00:04:50,373
Looks, wealth, and a great personality.

67
00:04:50,707 --> 00:04:51,916
By the way,

68
00:04:51,916 --> 00:04:53,293
aren't you close to your deadline?

69
00:04:54,836 --> 00:04:56,671
Yoon Jio, you're a devil!

70
00:04:58,423 --> 00:04:59,674
Are you stuck on something?

71
00:05:00,425 --> 00:05:01,259
Yeah.

72
00:05:02,802 --> 00:05:05,013
It's a romance web novel...

73
00:05:05,722 --> 00:05:07,056
but there's no romance.

74
00:05:07,932 --> 00:05:11,144
What do you think love is, Jio?

75
00:05:11,894 --> 00:05:13,438
Love is...

76
00:05:16,357 --> 00:05:19,360
seeping into someone else's world?

77
00:05:20,403 --> 00:05:23,239
Oh...

78
00:05:23,239 --> 00:05:24,782
Something like that, I guess?

79
00:05:38,421 --> 00:05:40,590
BADAM STAY

80
00:05:41,924 --> 00:05:43,885
This is a really wonderful place.

81
00:05:50,558 --> 00:05:51,768
This is ridiculous.

82
00:05:53,102 --> 00:05:55,271
With scenery like this...

83
00:05:55,521 --> 00:05:58,691
Do you also have a sentimental side, President?

84
00:06:00,318 --> 00:06:02,070
It'll definitely sell for a high price.

85
00:06:02,403 --> 00:06:03,196
What?

86
00:06:03,196 --> 00:06:05,448
Let's head in quickly,
I don't want to waste time.

87
00:06:32,266 --> 00:06:33,768
What brings you here?

88
00:06:46,364 --> 00:06:47,448
Are you an employee here?

89
00:06:48,074 --> 00:06:48,783
Yes.

90
00:06:50,118 --> 00:06:51,786
You don't have a reservation, do you?

91
00:06:51,786 --> 00:06:53,704
Please come this way, I'll show you around.

92
00:06:53,704 --> 00:06:54,789
What's your name?

93
00:06:55,456 --> 00:06:58,709
I'm the manager, Yoon Jio.

94
00:06:58,960 --> 00:07:00,002
Manager?

95
00:07:00,086 --> 00:07:03,798
Getting drunk during work hours and
turning this place into a dump makes you a manager?

96
00:07:03,798 --> 00:07:04,590
Excuse me?

97
00:07:05,091 --> 00:07:06,259
You said your name is Yoon Jio?

98
00:07:06,425 --> 00:07:08,970
You're fired, effective immediately.

99
00:07:09,720 --> 00:07:11,597
Who... are you?

100
00:07:16,602 --> 00:07:17,812
Cha Dokyung.

101
00:07:18,312 --> 00:07:19,730
The owner of this place.

102
00:07:30,074 --> 00:07:31,576
Glowing...

103
00:07:32,076 --> 00:07:33,411
His face is...

104
00:07:34,245 --> 00:07:35,705
practically glowing.

105
00:07:36,205 --> 00:07:38,708
It really is... glowing.

106
00:07:40,543 --> 00:07:42,044
From his face.

107
00:07:43,296 --> 00:07:44,130
What?

108
00:07:46,299 --> 00:07:47,800
- *Blegh*
- Ah, wait!

109
00:08:15,578 --> 00:08:22,043
Check In to You

